> I have to question the wisdom of converting a truck to electric, then
> immediately cramming a huge stereo in it...
>
> And a 40 mile range?  I guess it's a good thing it's a single cab; you
can
> keep your bicycle in the back...
>
> And the thing doesn't even have bumpers?
>
> Who was the yahoo that appraised this thing at $16,287.75?
>
> I like the phrase "The chassis is a rare and collectible VW classic,
which
> has undergone improvements above and beyond full restoration, as well
as
> conversion to electric power."  That's like saying "I drove to work
this
> morning, and then some!  I just drove south when I was supposed to be
> driving north!"
>
> Electric cars are fine, but they could have picked a crappy car to
start
> with..
>
> At 01:03 PM 4/4/99 -0700, Harry Houck wrote:
